{"type":"message","id":"f8b0ea62","parentId":"d5c11401","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:18:52.925Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The most recent log is `pulse_2026-03-24 091814.md`. Let me read it.","thinkingSignature":"30ab4d852e82383710ef630a9dcbc4f34616b4dc892b6de3e23634936fe866ca"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1rdjv4kq32b7_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-24 091814.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":632,"output":78,"cacheRead":12137,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12847,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774358330714}}
{"type":"message","id":"a672c2e2","parentId":"f8b0ea62","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:18:52.934Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_1rdjv4kq32b7_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 091814\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: tic/tic_classifier.py (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the next concrete action.\r\n\r\nFrom the goals:\r\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE\r\n- Phase 1 COMPLETE (Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec)\r\n- Phase 2 COMPLETE (Gap-Decay Synthesis)\r\n- Phase 3 COMPLETE (LLM-Augmented Pulse)\r\n\r\nThe current priority is the **TIC Experiment** (Temporal Invariance Compression):\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThe insight is that compression and causal discovery are the SAME problem. Causal structure IS invariant structure.\r\n\r\nThe next action should be to implement the TIC classifier. Let me look at what files exist and what I can do.\r\n\r\nFirst, I need to understand the pulse log files to implement the TIC experiment. Let me create a script or analysis that:\r\n1. Reads the pulse log files\r\n2. Identifies invariants (things that persist across pulses) vs variants (things that change)\r\n3. Uses these to predict next pulse content\r\n\r\nLet me write a PowerShell script for this experiment.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next priority. It requires implementing a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant structures across pulse logs and tests prediction accuracy. The pulse logs exist but need a script to analyze them.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier script that reads pulse logs, identifies invariant/variant patterns, and measures classification accuracy and next-pulse prediction success.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC Experiment - Temporal Invariance Compression\r\n# Phase 1 & 2 Unified: Compression = Causal Discovery\r\n# 2026-03-24\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$Lookback = 20,\r\n    [double]$Threshold = 0.7,\r\n    [string]$LogPattern = \"logs/pulse_*.md\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n\r\n# --- Configuration ---\r\n$PROJECT_ROOT = $PSScriptRoot\r\n$TIC_RESULTS = Join-Path $PROJECT_ROOT \"research/TIC_RESULTS.md\"\r\n$PULSE_DIR = Join-Path $PROJECT_ROOT \"logs\"\r\n\r\n# --- Step 1: Collect pulse logs ---\r\nWrite-Host \"[TIC] Collecting last $Lookback pulse logs...\"\r\n$pulseFiles = Get-ChildItem -Path $PULSE_DIR -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" |\r\n    Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending |\r\n    Select-Object -First $Lookback\r\n\r\nif ($pulseFiles.Count -lt 5) {\r\n    Write-Warning \"[TIC] Insufficient pulse logs ($($pulseFiles.Count) < 5). Need at least 5 for prediction test.\"\r\n    exit 1\r\n}\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"[TIC] Found $($pulseFiles.Count) pulse logs\"\r\n\r\n# --- Step 2: Extract content fingerprints ---\r\nfunction Get-ContentFingerprint($file) {\r\n    $content = Get-Content $file.FullName -Raw\r\n    # Extract key structural elements\r\n    $fingerprint = @{\r\n        File = $file.Name\r\n        Time = $file.LastWriteTime\r\n        Lines = ($content -split \"`n\").Count\r\n        Words = ($content -split \"\\s+\").Count\r\n        Sections = ([regex]::Matches($content, \"^## \")).Count\r\n        Goals = ([regex]::Matches($content, \"- \\[ \\]\")).Count\r\n        Done = ([regex]::Matches($content, \"- \\[x\\]\")).Count\r\n        Action = ([regex]::Matches($content, \"### ACTION\")).Count\r\n        Mutation = ([regex]::Matches($content, \"### MUTATION\")).Count\r\n        Hash = (Get-FileHash $file.FullName -Algorithm MD5).Hash\r\n    }\r\n    return $fingerprint\r\n}\r\n\r\n$fingerprints = $pulseFiles | ForEach-Object { Get-ContentFingerprint $_ }\r\n\r\n# --- Step 3: Identify INVARIANTS (persist across all pulses) ---\r\n$invariantFields = @()\r\n$allFields = @(\"Lines\", \"Words\", \"Sections\", \"Goals\", \"Done\", \"Action\", \"Mutation\")\r\n\r\nforeach ($field in $allFields) {\r\n    $values = $fingerprints | Select-Object -ExpandProperty $field\r\n    $avg = ($values | Measure-Object -Average).Average\r\n    $std = [Math]::Sqrt((($values | ForEach-Object { [Math]::Pow($_ - $avg, 2) }) | Measure-Object -Average).Average)\r\n    $cv = if ($avg -ne 0) { $std / $avg } else { 0 }\r\n    \r\n    # Low coefficient of variation = INVARIANT\r\n    if ($cv -lt 0.15) {\r\n        $invariantFields += @{\r\n            Field = $field\r\n            Avg = $avg\r\n            CV = $cv\r\n            Status = \"INVARIANT\"\r\n        }\r\n    } else {\r\n        $invariantFields += @{\r\n            Field = $field\r\n            Avg = $avg\r\n            CV = $cv\r\n            Status = \"VARIANT\"\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# --- Step 4: Identify VARIANTS (change between pulses) ---\r\n$variantFields = $invariantFields | Where-Object { $_.Status -eq \"VARIANT\" }\r\n\r\n# --- Step 5: Next-pulse PREDICTION test ---\r\n# Use first N-1 pulses to predict Nth\r\n$trainingSet = $fingerprints[0..($fingerprints.Count - 2)]\r\n$testPulse = $fingerprints[$fingerprints.Count - 1]\r\n\r\n# Predict based on invariant means\r\n$predictions = @{}\r\n$correctPredictions = 0\r\n$totalPredictions = 0\r\n\r\nforeach ($inv in $invariantFields\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 09:18:44\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774358332932}}
